#: ../../source/api/world_toolbar.md:1
msgid "World > Toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_toolbar.md:3
msgid ""
"Toolbars are regular worlds that are usually docked beside the main world "
"with `world.camera.add_right(toolbar)` or `world.camera.add_bottom(toolbar)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_toolbar.md:5
msgid ""
"They are especially useful together with buttons, because the active world "
"can react to toolbar actions in `on_message`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/api/world_toolbar.md:7
msgid "API Reference"
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds.worlds.gui.toolbar.Toolbar:1 of
msgid "A panel that holds buttons, labels, and other widgets."
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds.worlds.gui.toolbar.Toolbar:3 of
msgid ""
"Toolbars are usually docked beside the main world using "
"`world.camera.add_right(toolbar)` or `world.camera.add_bottom(toolbar)`. "
"Widgets are added with `toolbar.add(widget)` (or by simply creating them - "
"they register themselves automatically when their world is set to the "
"toolbar)."
msgstr ""

#: miniworlds.worlds.gui.toolbar.Toolbar:8 of
msgid ""
"When a button inside a toolbar is clicked it broadcasts its label text as a "
"message. The main world responds via `on_message`."
msgstr ""

